      "text": [
        " : «عَلَى اَلْإِمَامِ أَنْ يُصَلِّيَ اَلظُّهْرَ بِمِنًى ثُمَّ يَبِيتَ بِهَا وَ يُصْبِحَ حَتَّى تَطْلُعَ اَلشَّمْسُ ثُمَّ يَخْرُجَ إِلَى عَرَفَاتٍ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2976 - Jamil ibn Darraj narrated from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"It is incumbent upon the Imam to pray the Zuhr prayer in Mina, spend the night there, and remain until sunrise. Then, he should depart for Arafat.\""
        ]
      }
